毕苏斯基的主要目标之一是将波兰的政治体制由[[议会制|议会制]]转为[[总统制|总统制]]；但是，他反对引入[[极权主义|极权主义]]。<ref name="PWN"/>1935年4月，波兰新宪法（即[[四月宪法|四月宪法]]）得到采用，这部宪法是毕苏斯基的支持者根据毕苏斯基的要求所修改的，并且加大了总统的权力，但这样一部宪法来得太晚，毕苏斯基已经对总统一职不感兴趣；虽然如此，波兰直到[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]之前所采用的都是四月宪法，而[[波兰流亡政府|波兰流亡政府]]在二战时及战后也一直使用这部宪法。 

但是，相较于理性-法律权威而言，毕苏斯基统治波兰更依靠魅力型权威。<ref name="PWN"/>他的追随者中没有人会自称是他的合法继承人，他死后，[[萨纳齐亚|萨纳齐亚]]政体将会很快崩溃，而波兰将回到前毕苏斯基时代的议会政治竞争状态中。<ref name="PWN"/>

毕苏斯基开创了一个社会稳定的时代，而且这个时代占波兰第二共和国人口三分之一的[[少数民族|少数民族]]的情况有所好转。<ref name="Britannica" /><ref>[[#refStachura2004|Stachura 2004]], [http://books.google.com/books?id=BkKuir9oQYMC&pg=PA79&vq=%22one+in+three%22&dq=ethnic+minorities+Poland&sig=eK8N4FZvEBIahhqfaKXsFO8k2Sk 第79页].</ref><ref name="Columbia">{{cite web |url=http://encyclopedia2.tfd.com/Poland |title=Poland |accessdate=2007年12月29日 |work=[[哥伦比亚百科全书|哥伦比亚百科全书]] |archive-date=2013年1月4日 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130104221741/http://encyclopedia2.tfd.com/Poland |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Electronicmuseum">{{cite web|url=http://www.electronicmuseum.ca/Poland-WW2/ethnic_minorities_occupation/emo_intro.html |title=Poland's ethnic minorities and the Nazi-Soviet occupation of Poland |accessdate=2007年12月29日 |work=Poland's Holocaust |last=Piotrowski |first=Tadeusz |authorlink=Tadeusz Piotrowski （社会学家） |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080226104808/http://www.electronicmuseum.ca/Poland-WW2/ethnic_minorities_occupation/emo_intro.html |archivedate=2008年2月26日 }}</ref> 毕苏斯基将[[民族民主党|民族民主党]]的“[[波兰化|民族同化]]”政策转变为“国家意识统一”政策：公民不以他们的种族衡量，而是以他们对国家的忠心衡量。<ref name="Snyder">[[#refSnyder2004|Snyder 2004]], [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN030010586X&id=xSpEynLxJ1MC&pg=PA144&lpg=PA144&dq=stanislaw+grabski&sig=5kSKOnXipwsTitk7w_hotRTooPQ 第144页] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN030010586X&id=xSpEynLxJ1MC&pg=PA144&lpg=PA144&dq=stanislaw+grabski&sig=5kSKOnXipwsTitk7w_hotRTooPQ |date=20200820050114 }}.</ref><ref name="Zim166">Joshua D. Zimmerman, ''Poles, Jews, and the Politics of Nationality: The Bund and the Polish Socialist Party in Late Tsarist Russia, 1892-1914'', [[University_of_Wisconsin_Press|University of Wisconsin Press]], 2004, ISBN 978-0-299-19464-2 [http://books.google.com/books?id=6sbr9cZyw_4C&pg=PA166&dq=Pi%C5%82sudski+assimilate+Jews&as_brr=3&sig=ACfU3U16J8ETxYZsaglVOMIKN4o1nZ6Jkg Google Print, 第166页]</ref>他让“国家意识统一”政策同样适用于[[波兰犹太人|波兰犹太人]]，这种做法被广泛认为是他对民族民主党反犹政策的回应。<ref>David Vital. [http://books.google.com/books?id=XB1d1JhKoVUC&pg=PA788&dq=pilsudski+jews&sig=ACfU3U01aaaFOLXR8bI58Ydh7i8qAqMmnw ''A People Apart: The Jews in Europe, 1789-1939.''] Oxford University Press, 1999年.</ref><ref>Stanley G. Payne, ''A History of Fascism, 1914-1945'', [[University_of_Wisconsin_Press|University of Wisconsin Press]], 1995年, ISBN 978-0-299-14874-4, [http://books.google.com/books?id=NLiFIEdI1V4C&pg=PA141&dq=Pi%C5%82sudski+antisemite&ei=nii3SMfmAafKzAT1kOH_Bg&sig=ACfU3U0F52STeEQI7DGYWqM-VBWmnwpFZA Google Print, 第141页]</ref><ref>Anatol Lieven, ''The Baltic Revolution: Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania and the Path to Independence'', Yale University Press, 1993年, ISBN 978-0-300-06078-2, [http://books.google.com/books?id=iz3NACNOpCAC&pg=PA163&dq=Pi%C5%82sudski+antisemite&lr=&ei=ECm3SPjmL4y4yASx4-mbAw&sig=ACfU3U0TFJsLvGXn-CK8frgMRL7x_B-7SQ Google Print, 第163页]</ref><ref>Barbara Engelking-Boni, Barbara Engelking, Gunnar S. Paulsson, Emma Harris, ''Holocaust and Memory: The Experience of the Holocaust and Its Consequences : an Investigation Based on Personal Narratives'', Continuum International Publishing Group, 2001年, ISBN 978-0-7185-0159-4, [http://books.google.com/books?id=0oystlNB7JAC&pg=PA75&dq=Pi%C5%82sudski+antisemite&lr=&ei=ECm3SPjmL4y4yASx4-mbAw&sig=ACfU3U1JjHixPxrA3eC2SOtsvfwI9Jq04Q Google Print, 第175页]</ref><ref>Edward H. Flannery, ''The Anguish of the Jews: Twenty-Three Centuries of Antisemitism'', Paulist Press, 2005, ISBN 978-0-8091-4324-5, [http://books.google.com/books?id=r1ulI_N0zW8C&pg=PA200&dq=Pi%C5%82sudski+antisemite&lr=&ei=ECm3SPjmL4y4yASx4-mbAw&sig=ACfU3U0__xS1-7YHZ_0dFRljVtyjOpgJJg Google Print. 第200页] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=r1ulI_N0zW8C&pg=PA200&dq=Pi%C5%82sudski+antisemite&lr=&ei=ECm3SPjmL4y4yASx4-mbAw&sig=ACfU3U0__xS1-7YHZ_0dFRljVtyjOpgJJg |date=20160430213030 }}</ref><ref name="Zim19">Joshua D. Zimmerman, ''Contested Memories: Poles and Jews During the Holocaust and Its Aftermath'', Rutgers University Press, 2003, ISBN 978-0-8135-3158-8, [http://books.google.com/books?id=uHJyoGiep2gC&pg=PA19&dq=Pi%C5%82sudski+antisemite&ei=nii3SMfmAafKzAT1kOH_Bg&sig=ACfU3U0Z7JIF0Iow8Gq92Bs4O6l9mYONLw Google Print, 第19页]</ref><ref name="Snyder"/><ref name="Zim166"/><ref>{{cite book|last=Prizel|first=Ilya|year=1998年|title=National Identity and Foreign Policy|publisher=Cambridge University Press|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=fE2quB852jcC&pg=PA61&dq=pilsudski+jews+foreign+body&sig=ACfU3U2OGNAiwrAnCHLRh_xwEAAcF1fbEA}}</ref><ref>Beryl Wein. [http://books.google.com/books?id=11f9xBbOBBEC&pg=PA292&lpg=PA292&dq=%22foreign+body%22+pilsudski+pogrom+lwow&source=web&ots=wSzDpHFNEN&sig=JQHbhAGEQbcFvHrs4b3v7ekFouQ&hl=en&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=1&ct=result Triumph of Survival: The Story of the Jews in the Modern Era 1650-1990.] Mesorah Publications, 1990年.</ref>很多[[波兰犹太人|波兰犹太人]]对毕苏斯基时期（1926年至1935年）及毕苏斯基本人具有好感，而在毕苏斯基任命的总理[[卡齐米日·巴尔泰尔|卡齐米日·巴尔泰尔]]执政期间，这些犹太人的情况得到很大改善。<ref name="Cieplinski">{{cite web
